column5: Well Hello everyone  I've been wearing out the hardwood floors from pacing back and forth with the long awaited much anticipated Bass opener , so i thought I  would lop on a collection of photo's from the last couple of weeks......  Saturday June13th  Pike and Walleye on a Chartruese jig           24/7 with a small gator    The release as always    Canadian Beaver....    Red tailed Hawk    Bull Moose Shedding Stage    Same with this Red Fox    Ruby throated Humming Bird     Male Wood Duck    Blue Heron with a bullhead       Osprey       Scenery         :Gonefishing:
Very nice photographs. Thanks for sharing. Kenny G.
Wow!  Some very beautiful shots there Bud. Thanks for showing them.
Thanks for sharing. I love the Canadian Beaver.
Very nice shots.  I especially like the heron with fish in beak being chased by a redwing. One in a million shot!
Great wildlife shots
Wow, great pics.  Thanks for sharing.
Thanks for posting those beauties. Jim
very nice! what do you shoot with?
Canon Rebel xsi....( wifes ).....  :worthy: Canon sx 100 ( Mine )
Awesome pictures, thanks for sharing them.  Joey
Great photos WSB! Love the Hummingbird. We see clones of it at the cottage quite frequently. I'm always amazed at their flying abilities. Thanks for sharing.
Gorgeous Pictures!!  ....I love BEAVER too!
drove through northern ontario twice ! didnt see 1 moose..great pics!
Excellent pics Paul!!!
Incredible photos. Thanks for sharing.
Increadible pictures.  That's inspiring me to dust off the SLR, and bring it with me on some fishing trips.  Thanks,,
awesome trip congrats
Awesome photos. You have some great shots there. Nice fish BTW.
my pike rules them all!
absolutely amazing shots, nice variety.... thanks for postin those
Ahhhhhhhh....Nature Porn is the BEST!!!!!  Thanx...  Will

WOW.....you a proffessional photographer or what!? awesome pictures, had to show those to my wife......she thinks they are awesome too...she wants a better camera now....lol....so i guess i should say thank you!  Great report, thanks for sharing.
looks like it was an  enjoyable outing!~ good stuff bud!  Thank you for sharing
